# Manual Testing Guide: Starter CI/CD Flow

This guide walks through the same scenarios covered by the e2e tests, using CLI commands
that you can run manually against a local k8s stack.

## Prerequisites

```bash
# 1. Ensure k8s stack is running
./bin/eh status
# Should show: K8s Stack ✓

# 2. Set API URL
export EVE_API_URL=http://api.eve.lvh.me

# 3. Verify connectivity
eve health
# Should show API healthy
```

## Test 1: Connectivity Check

Verifies the Eve API is accessible.

```bash
# Health check
curl -s $EVE_API_URL/health | jq

# Expected: { "status": "ok", ... }

# Auth status
eve auth status --json

# Expected: Shows authentication state
```

## Test 2: Create Org and Project

Creates an org and project for testing.

```bash
# Create or ensure org exists
eve org ensure "manual-test-org" --json

# Note the org ID from output, then create project
eve project ensure \
  --org <ORG_ID> \
  --name "manual-test-project" \
  --slug mtest \
  --repo-url https://github.com/eve-horizon/eve-horizon-fullstack-example \
  --branch main \
  --force \
  --json

# Note the project ID for subsequent tests
export PROJECT_ID=<project_id_from_output>
```

## Test 3: Smoke Job (Basic Agent Execution)

Tests that a simple job can run with the mclaude harness.

```bash
# Create a job
eve job create \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --description "Run a quick smoke check: list top-level files and exit." \
  --harness mclaude \
  --json

# Note job ID from output
export JOB_ID=<job_id_from_output>

# Wait for completion (max 5 minutes)
eve job wait $JOB_ID --timeout 300

# Check result
eve job show $JOB_ID --json

# Expected: phase = "done"
```

## Test 4: Edit Tool Permission (Yolo Mode)

Tests that the Edit tool works with yolo permission policy.

```bash
# Create a job that uses Edit
eve job create \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --title "Test Edit tool permission" \
  --description "Read the README.md file and use the Edit tool to add a comment at the top." \
  --phase ready \
  --priority 0 \
  --json

# Follow the job to see real-time output
eve job follow <job_id>

# Expected: Job completes successfully (exit code 0)
# The logs should show:
#   - "permission":"yolo"
#   - "--dangerously-skip-permissions" in the command
#   - Edit tool succeeds
```

## Test 5: Pipeline Operations

### 5.1 List Pipelines

```bash
# List pipelines for the project
eve pipeline list $PROJECT_ID --json

# Expected: Shows pipelines defined in manifest (e.g., deploy-test, remediation)
```

### 5.2 Show Pipeline Details

```bash
# Get details of a specific pipeline
eve pipeline show $PROJECT_ID deploy-test --json

# Expected: Shows pipeline definition with trigger and steps
```

### 5.3 Run a Pipeline

```bash
# Run a pipeline (creates jobs for each step)
eve pipeline run deploy-test \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --ref main \
  --env test \
  --json

# Note the run ID from output
export RUN_ID=<run_id_from_output>

# Check the pipeline run
eve run show $PROJECT_ID $RUN_ID --json

# Expected: Shows run status with associated jobs
```

### 5.4 Pipeline Job Dependencies

```bash
# When a pipeline runs, jobs are created with dependencies
# - First step: phase = "ready"
# - Dependent steps: phase = "backlog" (waiting for dependencies)

eve job list --project $PROJECT_ID --json

# Filter for pipeline jobs
eve job list --project $PROJECT_ID --label pipeline:deploy-test
```

## Test 6: Workflow Operations

### 6.1 List Workflows

```bash
# List available workflows
eve workflow list $PROJECT_ID --json

# Expected: Shows workflows defined in manifest (e.g., manual-deploy)
```

### 6.2 Run Workflow (Fire and Forget)

```bash
# Run workflow without waiting
eve workflow run $PROJECT_ID manual-deploy \
  --input '{"test": true}' \
  --json

# Expected: Returns job_id immediately
```

### 6.3 Invoke Workflow (Wait for Result)

```bash
# Invoke workflow and wait for completion
eve workflow invoke $PROJECT_ID manual-deploy \
  --input '{"test": true}' \
  --json

# Expected: Returns job_id, status, and result when complete
```

## Test 7: Event System

### 7.1 Emit Event via CLI

```bash
# Emit a manual event
eve event emit \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --type manual.test \
  --source manual \
  --json

# Expected: Event created with ID and status
```

### 7.2 List Events

```bash
# List recent events
eve event list --project $PROJECT_ID --json

# Expected: Shows events including the one just emitted
```

### 7.3 Event-Triggered Pipeline

If the manifest has a pipeline with `trigger.system.event`:

```bash
# Emit an event that triggers a pipeline
eve event emit \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --type job.failed \
  --source system \
  --json

# Check if pipeline was triggered
eve run list $PROJECT_ID --json
```

## Test 8: Git Controls

Tests job-level git configuration.

```bash
# Create a job with git controls
eve job create \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --title "Test git controls" \
  --description "Make a small change and commit it" \
  --git '{"branch": "test-git-controls", "create_branch": "always", "commit": "auto"}' \
  --json

# Follow the job
eve job follow <job_id>

# Expected: Job creates branch, makes changes, commits them
```

## Test 9: Remediation Pipeline (Event-Triggered)

The remediation pipeline triggers on job failures.

```bash
# 1. Create a job that will fail
eve job create \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --title "Intentional failure" \
  --description "Exit with an error to test remediation" \
  --json

# 2. Wait for it to fail
eve job wait <job_id> --timeout 120

# 3. Check if remediation pipeline was triggered
eve event list --project $PROJECT_ID --type job.failed --json
eve run list $PROJECT_ID --json

# Expected: A remediation pipeline run should be created
```

## Cleanup

```bash
# Cancel any running jobs
eve job list --project $PROJECT_ID --phase active
eve job cancel <job_ids>

# Optionally delete test project
# eve project delete $PROJECT_ID
```

## Troubleshooting

### Job stuck in "active" phase

```bash
# Check runner pods
kubectl get pods -n eve | grep runner

# Check job logs
eve job logs <job_id>

# Follow job output
eve job follow <job_id>
```

### Permission errors

```bash
# Verify auth status
eve auth status --json

# Re-authenticate if needed
eve auth login
```

### Pipeline not triggering

```bash
# Check manifest is synced
eve project sync

# Verify pipeline definition
eve pipeline show $PROJECT_ID <pipeline_name> --json

# Check event was emitted
eve event list --project $PROJECT_ID --json
```

### Harness errors ("only prompt commands supported")

This error occurred with `permission: 'default'` and has been fixed.
Jobs now default to `permission: 'yolo'` which works in streaming mode.

If you see this error:
1. Ensure you're running the latest stack: `./bin/eh k8s deploy`
2. Check the job's permission policy: `eve job show <id> --json`
